    <h2>Information We Gather </h2>
    <p>  The majority of the information we gather comes directly from you when you register to use the site, fill out forms, or sign up for one of our programs. In addition, we track any postings you make to our blogs or forums, your interactions with other E pro users, and your conversations with E pro itself. Additionally, as you access, browse, read, or otherwise use the Site, we automatically gather information about you. We also get information from third-party vendors and other available sources..
    </p>
   
    <h2>Our Legal Justification for Using Your Personal Data  </h2>
    <p>All processing of your personal information shall be supported by a "lawful ground" for processing, which is described below, when applicable under applicable legislation.
    </p>
    <h2>How Will We Use the Data Gathered?   </h2>
    <p>We use personal information to operate the Site, comprehend how users interact with the Site, and fulfill our obligations to you. We also use it to protect the integrity and security of the marketplace, prevent fraud, contact you and send you direct marketing communications, advertise the Site, our services, and the E-Pro marketplace, respond to legal requests from public authorities, and comply with applicable laws and regulations.
    </p>
    
<h2>How Long Do We Keep Personal Information </h2>
<p>We will only retain personal information for as long as is necessary to achieve the above objectives. We do, however, occasionally save personal data for longer periods of time.</p>
<h2>Children  </h2>
<p>Only users who are at least 18 years old and of legal age to enter into legally binding contracts are granted access to this site. Only accounts owned by parents or legal guardians with the necessary permission may be used by minors under 18 and at least 13 years old to access the Site. The Site and the E-pro services are not available to minors under the age of 13. Children under 13 are not knowingly subject to our collection of personal information.</p>
<h2>Sharing Personal Information with Third Parties  </h2>
<p> In order to operate the Site, offer you our services, fulfill our legal and regulatory duties, and stop fraud, infractions, and illegal acts, we share personal information with third parties.</p>

<h2>Where We Store Personal Information </h2>
<p>Some of the personal information you give us may be held or processed on our behalf by outside suppliers and data processors who may be based in countries like Israel and the United States.</p>


<h2>Cookies  </h2>
<p>To enhance and personalize your experience, deliver our services, evaluate the effectiveness of our websites, and conduct marketing campaigns, we utilize cookies and related technologies (such as web beacons, pixels, tags, and scripts).</p>
<h2>External Links </h2>
<p>If you leave the Site and visit a third-party website, the information you give to that website and how it is used by the third party are not under "E- pro's" control and are not covered by this Policy.</p>
<h2>Security  </h2>
We utilize industry-standard technologies and internal policies to preserve the security of the Site and your personal information and to prevent unauthorized access, loss, misuse, alteration, destruction, or damage to it.
<h2>Personal Information Updating  </h2>
<p>We take steps to ensure that the personal information we collect is correct and current, and we give you the option to update your information through your account profile settings. Please let us know right away if you think your information is erroneous or incorrect in any other manner.</p>
<h2>Payment Information</h2>
<p>If you use the Service to make or receive payments, we will also collect certain payment information, such as credit card or other financial account information, and billing address.</p>
Feedback	
<p>About their interactions with other E-pro Users of our Service, E-pro Users provide us with both public and private comments. Please be aware that any public comments you make on the Service about your interactions with other E-pro Users or that other Users make about you are publicly available on the Service. Rarely, we may delete feedback in accordance with the applicable clauses of our Terms of Service, including the Terms of Use. Private comments that you make on the Service about your interactions with other E-pro Users or that other Users make about you won't be publicly available on the Service. Additionally, we gather user reviews of our service. We use this information to respond to your inquiries, improve the Service and how our Site functions, and develop new products and features.</p>

